name: Will You Go, Lassie, Go?
comments: Recorded by Peter Kennedy on July 7, 1952 at the O'Boyle family home in Belfast. Charles O'Boyle had invited a number of performers to meet Peter Kennedy for his first evening of music collecting in Belfast. When Peter Kennedy returned to London, he persuaded George Martin and the educational dept. of the Gramophone Company to issue this track on the 10" LP "Folk Song Today".
